{
  "abstract": "Soil sampling is one of the most important prerequisites to implement site-specific nutrient management.\r\nIt is also the weakest link in the whole chain of soil test-based nutrient management. A small quantity of\r\nsoil (about 500 g) collected should truly represent the millions of tons of soil in a field. Hence, utmost care\r\nshould be taken during collection to secure accurate results",
